UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Get on up there and start digging!$B$BI\'ve got places to go and people to see -- time is money!' WHERE entry=2987; -- RequestItemsText: Get on up there and start digging!$B$BI\'ve got places to go and people to see -- time is money!
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Have you searched the cages, $N? We must find Sharpbeak!',ObjectiveText1_loc2='Check First Cage',ObjectiveText2_loc2='Check Second Cage' WHERE entry=2988; -- RequestItemsText: Have you searched the cages, $N? We must find Sharpbeak! -- ObjectiveText1: Check First Cage -- ObjectiveText2: Check Second Cage
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Hurry, $N!  If the Vilebranch trolls have Sharpbeak, then who knows what they might be doing with him!' WHERE entry=2989; -- RequestItemsText: Hurry, $N!  If the Vilebranch trolls have Sharpbeak, then who knows what they might be doing with him! -- EndText: Search the Altar of Zul
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='$N, you come bearing a gift?' WHERE entry=2990; -- RequestItemsText: $N, you come bearing a gift?
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Do you have Nekrum\'s Medallion, $N?  There are powers hidden within it that I am eager to discover.' WHERE entry=2991; -- RequestItemsText: Do you have Nekrum\'s Medallion, $N?  There are powers hidden within it that I am eager to discover.
UPDATE locales_quest SET  WHERE entry=2992; -- EndText: Wait for Grimshade to finish
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Save Sharpbeak!',ObjectiveText2_loc2='Open Sharpbeak\'s Cage' WHERE entry=2994; -- RequestItemsText: Save Sharpbeak! -- ObjectiveText2: Open Sharpbeak\'s Cage
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Keeping the Highvale elves isolated is the key. Have you found the lodge?',ObjectiveText1_loc2='Burn the Highvale Records',ObjectiveText2_loc2='Burn the Highvale Notes' WHERE entry=2995; -- RequestItemsText: Keeping the Highvale elves isolated is the key. Have you found the lodge? -- ObjectiveText1: Burn the Highvale Records -- ObjectiveText2: Burn the Highvale Notes
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='What have you brought me, $R?' WHERE entry=3002; -- RequestItemsText: What have you brought me, $R?
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Another shipment from Curgle, I assume?' WHERE entry=3022; -- RequestItemsText: Another shipment from Curgle, I assume?
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Did you bring me the temper, $N?' WHERE entry=3042; -- RequestItemsText: Did you bring me the temper, $N?
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='The hate that Edana spreads across the land must be stopped.' WHERE entry=3062; -- RequestItemsText: The hate that Edana spreads across the land must be stopped.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='The wings of the Northspring harpies are black as the night; do not take your eyes off of them, lest they disappear into darkness.' WHERE entry=3063; -- RequestItemsText: The wings of the Northspring harpies are black as the night; do not take your eyes off of them, lest they disappear into darkness.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Another $R to bolster the ranks. Good enough for me.$B$BYou\'ll probably have a hard time hefting a good weapon like an axe, but a spear\'s just as good as anything else.$B$BWelcome to the Valley of Trials.' WHERE entry=3065; -- RequestItemsText: Another $R to bolster the ranks. Good enough for me.$B$BYou\'ll probably have a hard time hefting a good weapon like an axe, but a spear\'s just as good as anything else.$B$BWelcome to the Valley of Trials.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Jen\'shan see a mighty $C before her and da spirits approve.$B$BDa path of da $C is one of our oldest walks of life. Da Horde turned to us when they be just strugglin\' to survive on Azeroth, and they ask us to teach them, to show them the secrets of many tings. They were strong already: strong in shaman ways; strong in warrior ways. But the hunter path not be their path... then.' WHERE entry=3082; -- RequestItemsText: Jen\'shan see a mighty $C before her and da spirits approve.$B$BDa path of da $C is one of our oldest walks of life. Da Horde turned to us when they be just strugglin\' to survive on Azeroth, and they ask us to teach them, to show them the secrets of many tings. They were strong already: strong in shaman ways; strong in warrior ways. But the hunter path not be their path... then.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Welcome to the Valley of Trials, Rangrang. You wouldn\'t be here if you hadn\'t gotten my tablet, so I will get to the point.$B$BI am Rwag and I am responsible for training the rogues, thieves, and cutpurses here in the Valley. I\'m the one the Hand will turn to if you\'re not ready for what\'s to come. But don\'t worry, the Hand won\'t be controlling everything you do, but it would be wise to work with them if they have need of your talents.' WHERE entry=3083; -- RequestItemsText: Welcome to the Valley of Trials, Rangrang. You wouldn\'t be here if you hadn\'t gotten my tablet, so I will get to the point.$B$BI am Rwag and I am responsible for training the rogues, thieves, and cutpurses here in the Valley. I\'m the one the Hand will turn to if you\'re not ready for what\'s to come. But don\'t worry, the Hand won\'t be controlling everything you do, but it would be wise to work with them if they have need of your talents.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Ah, welcome, $N. I\'m pleased you have arrived. My days have become long and even busy what with so many students to teach, but the coming of one of your ilk brings me a great sense of accomplishment--I remember the days when I was taught by one of your shamans.' WHERE entry=3084; -- RequestItemsText: Ah, welcome, $N. I\'m pleased you have arrived. My days have become long and even busy what with so many students to teach, but the coming of one of your ilk brings me a great sense of accomplishment--I remember the days when I was taught by one of your shamans.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='So ya made it... good good! Da spirits tol\' me you be comin\' to see Ken\'jai soon enough. Let me be one o\' da first to welcome ya to da Valley of Trials. Dis place not be your home fer long, but while it is, why dontcha make da best o\' it.' WHERE entry=3085; -- RequestItemsText: So ya made it... good good! Da spirits tol\' me you be comin\' to see Ken\'jai soon enough. Let me be one o\' da first to welcome ya to da Valley of Trials. Dis place not be your home fer long, but while it is, why dontcha make da best o\' it.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Ya look to please Mai\'ah already, $N. Dat be good. You give Mai\'ah respect, and Mai\'ah maybe give you respect back. But enough o\' dat, you be here to learn \'bout magic, not hear Mai\'ah talk.$B$BThere be only one ting Mai\'ah can no teach you \'bout magic, $N, and dat\'s how to stop da corruptin\'.' WHERE entry=3086; -- RequestItemsText: Ya look to please Mai\'ah already, $N. Dat be good. You give Mai\'ah respect, and Mai\'ah maybe give you respect back. But enough o\' dat, you be here to learn \'bout magic, not hear Mai\'ah talk.$B$BThere be only one ting Mai\'ah can no teach you \'bout magic, $N, and dat\'s how to stop da corruptin\'.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Ah, so you come at last. Good. Jen\'shan be waitin\' for you.$B$BMany tink it be an easy path, but Jen\'shan tell you dat not true. Mastering da beasts of Durotar and beyond take as much skill as masterin\' the arcane arts or speakin\' to our ancestors.$B$BFirin\' a bow or rifle may not be as dangerous to you as castin\' a spell, but it sure be as dangerous to your enemy.' WHERE entry=3087; -- RequestItemsText: Ah, so you come at last. Good. Jen\'shan be waitin\' for you.$B$BMany tink it be an easy path, but Jen\'shan tell you dat not true. Mastering da beasts of Durotar and beyond take as much skill as masterin\' the arcane arts or speakin\' to our ancestors.$B$BFirin\' a bow or rifle may not be as dangerous to you as castin\' a spell, but it sure be as dangerous to your enemy.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Shhh, not so loud. I don\'t trust Nartok over there. Anyone that has to hide deeper in a cave than I do shouldn\'t be trifled with.$B$BI trust you had no problem finding your way around?' WHERE entry=3088; -- RequestItemsText: Shhh, not so loud. I don\'t trust Nartok over there. Anyone that has to hide deeper in a cave than I do shouldn\'t be trifled with.$B$BI trust you had no problem finding your way around?
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='So, you\'ve arrived. I was beginning to wonder when you would show yourself. I sent the parchment some time ago--I wasn\'t sure if it had arrived.$B$BBut enough chatter... you\'re here because you have been chosen, chosen to lead the spiritual lives of our people.' WHERE entry=3089; -- RequestItemsText: So, you\'ve arrived. I was beginning to wonder when you would show yourself. I sent the parchment some time ago--I wasn\'t sure if it had arrived.$B$BBut enough chatter... you\'re here because you have been chosen, chosen to lead the spiritual lives of our people.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Finally, you\'ve arrived... and discretely also. Good.$B$BOur world is full of fools, Asatokta. Even the mighty Thrall has greater flaws than most can see. He turns his back on the power needed to make this land ours completely! We\'re not the same people who were manipulated and used by creatures from the Nether. We are our own people. We are proud... and we are strong.' WHERE entry=3090; -- RequestItemsText: Finally, you\'ve arrived... and discretely also. Good.$B$BOur world is full of fools, Asatokta. Even the mighty Thrall has greater flaws than most can see. He turns his back on the power needed to make this land ours completely! We\'re not the same people who were manipulated and used by creatures from the Nether. We are our own people. We are proud... and we are strong.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Ah, at last, you\'ve arrived, $C. I did not lie in my note, $N. We are a special breed also, not unlike the druids or shamans of our tribe. You are just as important. We are the ones called upon to defend our borders, to hunt the centaur, and to go to war.' WHERE entry=3091; -- RequestItemsText: Ah, at last, you\'ve arrived, $C. I did not lie in my note, $N. We are a special breed also, not unlike the druids or shamans of our tribe. You are just as important. We are the ones called upon to defend our borders, to hunt the centaur, and to go to war.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Welcome to Camp Narache, $N. I hear good things about you. Your bloodline is strong, and many of the elders consider you skilled already. But that we will test.$B$BThe plains of Mulgore will be your home for sometime--you should do your best to learn it very well. One day you will travel to unfamilar lands to master greater skills. You must be ready.' WHERE entry=3092; -- RequestItemsText: Welcome to Camp Narache, $N. I hear good things about you. Your bloodline is strong, and many of the elders consider you skilled already. But that we will test.$B$BThe plains of Mulgore will be your home for sometime--you should do your best to learn it very well. One day you will travel to unfamilar lands to master greater skills. You must be ready.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='As quickly as water falls from the sky, here you are before me. I am pleased by your haste. It means you realize both the importance of our meeting and you being here. I am no leader, but I do understand the elements, and I can speak to the spirits of our people. I will teach you to do the same.' WHERE entry=3093; -- RequestItemsText: As quickly as water falls from the sky, here you are before me. I am pleased by your haste. It means you realize both the importance of our meeting and you being here. I am no leader, but I do understand the elements, and I can speak to the spirits of our people. I will teach you to do the same.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='You have arrived. This is good. Our ancestors\' spirits have become restless throughout Mulgore and beyond, but I cannot tell why. It will forever be your duty to learn to listen to nature\'s spirits, and act as their avatar. Be mindful of that.' WHERE entry=3094; -- RequestItemsText: You have arrived. This is good. Our ancestors\' spirits have become restless throughout Mulgore and beyond, but I cannot tell why. It will forever be your duty to learn to listen to nature\'s spirits, and act as their avatar. Be mindful of that.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Ah, so you\'ve arrived. Good. I overheard that a few others were able to escape "death" and were heading into town. Perhaps that resilence will pay off in the future also.$B$BYou may thank Sylvanas for your freedom... freedom of mind and body. Though you still remain tortured by the plague and its effects, you are now free to come and go as you see fit.' WHERE entry=3095; -- RequestItemsText: Ah, so you\'ve arrived. Good. I overheard that a few others were able to escape "death" and were heading into town. Perhaps that resilence will pay off in the future also.$B$BYou may thank Sylvanas for your freedom... freedom of mind and body. Though you still remain tortured by the plague and its effects, you are now free to come and go as you see fit.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='So you\'ve made it? Good, we\'ll have need of more rogues as time goes on. The Shadowstalkers will probably wind up finding you when they think the time\'s right, so don\'t go and slip up or do anything you might regret. They need talented agents... not pickpockets and fools.' WHERE entry=3096; -- RequestItemsText: So you\'ve made it? Good, we\'ll have need of more rogues as time goes on. The Shadowstalkers will probably wind up finding you when they think the time\'s right, so don\'t go and slip up or do anything you might regret. They need talented agents... not pickpockets and fools.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Ah, so between fire, plague, rioting, and much worse, one more of the "faithful" comes to my door. Well, let me bid you welcome, $C. And allow me a moment to explain a thing or two before you decide it\'s time for you to seek whatever drives you forward: the Holy Light no longer concerns you, the spirits of your forefathers are fairy tales, and creatures from the Nether don\'t want you.$B$BDo you understand me so far?' WHERE entry=3097; -- RequestItemsText: Ah, so between fire, plague, rioting, and much worse, one more of the "faithful" comes to my door. Well, let me bid you welcome, $C. And allow me a moment to explain a thing or two before you decide it\'s time for you to seek whatever drives you forward: the Holy Light no longer concerns you, the spirits of your forefathers are fairy tales, and creatures from the Nether don\'t want you.$B$BDo you understand me so far?
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='I knew you would come to me, $N. Not because you do not have the will to follow your own path, but because we are kindred spirits. We both have felt pain. We have both suffered. And now we want the power to take back what we know is ours: this land, our lives, our destinies. But there is much for you to learn still.' WHERE entry=3098; -- RequestItemsText: I knew you would come to me, $N. Not because you do not have the will to follow your own path, but because we are kindred spirits. We both have felt pain. We have both suffered. And now we want the power to take back what we know is ours: this land, our lives, our destinies. But there is much for you to learn still.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='I bid you welcome, $gbrother:sister;. I knew you would come. It was only a matter of time.$B$BWhat I said interested you, didn\'t it? I hit a chord... something inside you knew what I claimed was truth. Good.$B$BKnow this though: I am no traitor to Sylvanas. If anything, she would appreciate my claims considering it was her own beliefs that has put the Forsaken in the position it is now.' WHERE entry=3099; -- RequestItemsText: I bid you welcome, $gbrother:sister;. I knew you would come. It was only a matter of time.$B$BWhat I said interested you, didn\'t it? I hit a chord... something inside you knew what I claimed was truth. Good.$B$BKnow this though: I am no traitor to Sylvanas. If anything, she would appreciate my claims considering it was her own beliefs that has put the Forsaken in the position it is now.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Ah, you got my letter, $N... good.$B$BThere\'s been an influx of warriors in Elwynn recently - which is good for Stormwind, but bad for the kobolds and Defias in the area.' WHERE entry=3100; -- RequestItemsText: Ah, you got my letter, $N... good.$B$BThere\'s been an influx of warriors in Elwynn recently - which is good for Stormwind, but bad for the kobolds and Defias in the area.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Finally! We meet face to face, brother to brother. I welcome you to Northshire. This will be your home for a short time while you learn the ins and outs of how things are done, but know that Stormwind is not far off, and sooner or later, your path will take you there. But until then, be patient... Knight of the Silver Hand.' WHERE entry=3101; -- RequestItemsText: Finally! We meet face to face, brother to brother. I welcome you to Northshire. This will be your home for a short time while you learn the ins and outs of how things are done, but know that Stormwind is not far off, and sooner or later, your path will take you there. But until then, be patient... Knight of the Silver Hand.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='You made it here in one piece, and it doesn\'t look like too many people saw you. Good enough for me. I don\'t like to have much attention drawn to me back here... nice and quiet. I\'m sure you can understand.$B$BHave any trouble yet? I\'m glad to hear not. That\'ll change soon enough.' WHERE entry=3102; -- RequestItemsText: You made it here in one piece, and it doesn\'t look like too many people saw you. Good enough for me. I don\'t like to have much attention drawn to me back here... nice and quiet. I\'m sure you can understand.$B$BHave any trouble yet? I\'m glad to hear not. That\'ll change soon enough.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Ah, at last you\'ve come. I knew you would find your way to me. The Holy Light shines upon you, and the path you\'ve chosen. These times are harsh--the Burning Legion still has a presence upon Azeroth, the entirety of Kalimdor seeks new ways to defend itself from its own tribulations, and it is up to you to aid as many as you can.' WHERE entry=3103; -- RequestItemsText: Ah, at last you\'ve come. I knew you would find your way to me. The Holy Light shines upon you, and the path you\'ve chosen. These times are harsh--the Burning Legion still has a presence upon Azeroth, the entirety of Kalimdor seeks new ways to defend itself from its own tribulations, and it is up to you to aid as many as you can.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Hello, $N. I am Khelden. Is there something I can do for you?' WHERE entry=3104; -- RequestItemsText: Hello, $N. I am Khelden. Is there something I can do for you?
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Ah, so you\'ve arrived, and not a moment too soon, $N. Some of the guards were over here a moment ago and were giving me curious looks... pathetic mundanes.' WHERE entry=3105; -- RequestItemsText: Ah, so you\'ve arrived, and not a moment too soon, $N. Some of the guards were over here a moment ago and were giving me curious looks... pathetic mundanes.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Blast it\'s cold today, aint it? It\'s like the snow never goes away, $N.$B$BYou\'ve probably noticed already, but there are gnomes now living in our city. That\'s because they went and got themselves blown out of their own home. Don\'t go spreadin\' this \'round, but I can hardly blame them--I think I woulda resorted to explosives too if Ironforge were infested with Dark Irons or the like.' WHERE entry=3106; -- RequestItemsText: Blast it\'s cold today, aint it? It\'s like the snow never goes away, $N.$B$BYou\'ve probably noticed already, but there are gnomes now living in our city. That\'s because they went and got themselves blown out of their own home. Don\'t go spreadin\' this \'round, but I can hardly blame them--I think I woulda resorted to explosives too if Ironforge were infested with Dark Irons or the like.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='So, you\'ve made it! And not a second too soon. There\'s much to be done in Coldridge Valley and beyond. I\'m gonna need your help as much as you\'re gonna need mine!$B$BYou\'re a Knight of the Silver Hand now, be ready to play the part.' WHERE entry=3107; -- RequestItemsText: So, you\'ve made it! And not a second too soon. There\'s much to be done in Coldridge Valley and beyond. I\'m gonna need your help as much as you\'re gonna need mine!$B$BYou\'re a Knight of the Silver Hand now, be ready to play the part.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Ya made it! Good to hear! Betcha didn\'t have to track me to find the place either. Haha!$B$BOur profession is pretty steeped in tradition, $N. Learning the ways of the land. Learning to track a bear through the mountains. Even just surviving on wits alone takes a great deal of courage and cunning. Think you\'re capable?' WHERE entry=3108; -- RequestItemsText: Ya made it! Good to hear! Betcha didn\'t have to track me to find the place either. Haha!$B$BOur profession is pretty steeped in tradition, $N. Learning the ways of the land. Learning to track a bear through the mountains. Even just surviving on wits alone takes a great deal of courage and cunning. Think you\'re capable?
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='You made it! Great!$B$BWe\'ve got an influx of activity lately, so I\'m glad to count another of the Ironforge clan among our numbers. Too many of us are lookin\' to the arcane, and divine for my own tastes. Nothin\' against them and their beliefs, but there\'s nothing like a cold blade in your hand and a shadow to keep you from the light, know what I mean?' WHERE entry=3109; -- RequestItemsText: You made it! Great!$B$BWe\'ve got an influx of activity lately, so I\'m glad to count another of the Ironforge clan among our numbers. Too many of us are lookin\' to the arcane, and divine for my own tastes. Nothin\' against them and their beliefs, but there\'s nothing like a cold blade in your hand and a shadow to keep you from the light, know what I mean?
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Ach! Ya made it, $N! Wonderful!$B$BI was gonna say, I was about to lose faith that ye\'d arrive at all... get it, lose faith? It\'s a joke, lass... aww, nevermind. Ya didn\'t come here for me bad jokes anyway.' WHERE entry=3110; -- RequestItemsText: Ach! Ya made it, $N! Wonderful!$B$BI was gonna say, I was about to lose faith that ye\'d arrive at all... get it, lose faith? It\'s a joke, lass... aww, nevermind. Ya didn\'t come here for me bad jokes anyway.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Ah, well, another memorandum from a $R on a mission... isn\'t this quaint.$B$BNo, no, I ain\'t teasin\' ya, little one. Gotta respect your tenacity, that much is fer sure. I\'d be just as peeved if Ironforge was taken by Dark Iron dwarves, so don\'t be thinkin\' I don\'t feel for your plight...' WHERE entry=3112; -- RequestItemsText: Ah, well, another memorandum from a $R on a mission... isn\'t this quaint.$B$BNo, no, I ain\'t teasin\' ya, little one. Gotta respect your tenacity, that much is fer sure. I\'d be just as peeved if Ironforge was taken by Dark Iron dwarves, so don\'t be thinkin\' I don\'t feel for your plight...
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Glad to see you got my note and came over. Sorry about pretendin\' it was a memorandum from your higher-ups... no offense intended. I just knew the two of us, along with others of our kind, gotta stick together.$B$BNot many think it\'s the best thing in the world to have your kind and my kind holed up in the same city, but I think we can work things out just fine. What do you think?' WHERE entry=3113; -- RequestItemsText: Glad to see you got my note and came over. Sorry about pretendin\' it was a memorandum from your higher-ups... no offense intended. I just knew the two of us, along with others of our kind, gotta stick together.$B$BNot many think it\'s the best thing in the world to have your kind and my kind holed up in the same city, but I think we can work things out just fine. What do you think?
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Yeah, what\'s that, $R? Speak up, if you don\'t mind. I don\'t hear so good after a few ales.' WHERE entry=3114; -- RequestItemsText: Yeah, what\'s that, $R? Speak up, if you don\'t mind. I don\'t hear so good after a few ales.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Wonderful! You got my memorandum obviously.$B$BIgnore the fools around you, $N. The Holy Light?! The sword and shield?! These aren\'t paths for ones as open minded as us. Look at what "normal" magic did to our home. Coupled with those damned tinkerers, our race almost became extinct. And now we have to rely on the dwarves-- they\'d rather spend time allying with humans than help us rebuild our own home. We\'re like second-class citizens. Have you seen the way they look at us?' WHERE entry=3115; -- RequestItemsText: Wonderful! You got my memorandum obviously.$B$BIgnore the fools around you, $N. The Holy Light?! The sword and shield?! These aren\'t paths for ones as open minded as us. Look at what "normal" magic did to our home. Coupled with those damned tinkerers, our race almost became extinct. And now we have to rely on the dwarves-- they\'d rather spend time allying with humans than help us rebuild our own home. We\'re like second-class citizens. Have you seen the way they look at us?
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='You made it. I\'m so glad.$B$BMuch has happened over the last few years, Saric: the creation of Teldrassil, the corruption of many of the forest creatures here and abroad, discovery of lands we thought lost to us like Feralas... so much, in so little time. But those are just some of the reasons we are here, the most important being to protect our kind from further evil.' WHERE entry=3116; -- RequestItemsText: You made it. I\'m so glad.$B$BMuch has happened over the last few years, Saric: the creation of Teldrassil, the corruption of many of the forest creatures here and abroad, discovery of lands we thought lost to us like Feralas... so much, in so little time. But those are just some of the reasons we are here, the most important being to protect our kind from further evil.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='You\'ve arrived, and none too soon, $N. Welcome to Shadowglen.$B$BI trust my sigil found you in good spirits and health?$B$BAs I said previously, I am here to train you as a $C; to tame beasts to aid you in battle; to use a bow with unerring accuracy; to respect the lands which we call home and also the lands beyond.' WHERE entry=3117; -- RequestItemsText: You\'ve arrived, and none too soon, $N. Welcome to Shadowglen.$B$BI trust my sigil found you in good spirits and health?$B$BAs I said previously, I am here to train you as a $C; to tame beasts to aid you in battle; to use a bow with unerring accuracy; to respect the lands which we call home and also the lands beyond.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Hello, Ferlis. I\'m glad you found me. I was thinking that perhaps you got lost on the way here.$B$BNothing really new has happened in Shadowglen since I sent you my sigil, but I\'ll leave all the information gathering to you. Speak to the rest of the people around Aldrassil if you\'d like.' WHERE entry=3118; -- RequestItemsText: Hello, Ferlis. I\'m glad you found me. I was thinking that perhaps you got lost on the way here.$B$BNothing really new has happened in Shadowglen since I sent you my sigil, but I\'ll leave all the information gathering to you. Speak to the rest of the people around Aldrassil if you\'d like.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='It pleases me to see you\'ve arrived so quickly, $N. Welcome.$B$BAs you\'ve probably heard, all of Teldrassil is stirring with the comings and goings of travelers. Even members of the Alliance have even been allowed access onto Teldrassil\'s boughs in order to meet with other Kaldorei who prepare for the adventures ahead.' WHERE entry=3119; -- RequestItemsText: It pleases me to see you\'ve arrived so quickly, $N. Welcome.$B$BAs you\'ve probably heard, all of Teldrassil is stirring with the comings and goings of travelers. Even members of the Alliance have even been allowed access onto Teldrassil\'s boughs in order to meet with other Kaldorei who prepare for the adventures ahead.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Ah, young $C. I see you\'re eager to continue your studies. Good.$B$BI wonder, have you spent much time in the Emerald Dream already? Perhaps you\'re not prepared for that yet... In time, I\'m sure.$B$BBut until then, we should discuss other matters.' WHERE entry=3120; -- RequestItemsText: Ah, young $C. I see you\'re eager to continue your studies. Good.$B$BI wonder, have you spent much time in the Emerald Dream already? Perhaps you\'re not prepared for that yet... In time, I\'m sure.$B$BBut until then, we should discuss other matters.
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Yes?' WHERE entry=3121; -- RequestItemsText: Yes?
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Have you spoken to Neeru?' WHERE entry=3122; -- RequestItemsText: Have you spoken to Neeru?
UPDATE locales_quest SET RequestItemsText_loc2='Were you able to capture the wildkin?$B$BIf you succeed, we will be ready to shrink and capture the muisek of creatures of Feralas.' WHERE entry=3123; -- RequestItemsText: Were you able to capture the wildkin?$B$BIf you succeed, we will be ready to shrink and capture the muisek of creatures of Feralas.
